00:05:18.380 --> 00:05:20.030
J-Jotaro?

00:05:20.030 --> 00:05:20.720
Oh?

00:05:21.080 --> 00:05:24.000
Hey, Jotaro! Why are you sitting down?

00:05:24.000 --> 00:05:27.350
I'll defeat him! I'm next!

00:05:27.810 --> 00:05:34.080
Old man, have you played any one of
these games more than Kakyoin has?

00:05:36.670 --> 00:05:38.180
Stay out of this, old man.

00:05:38.530 --> 00:05:41.150
This isn't like playing cards or hanafuda.

00:05:43.690 --> 00:05:45.290
Next is baseball.

00:05:45.660 --> 00:05:49.460
I want you to play this baseball game with me.

00:05:51.160 --> 00:05:53.460
I'll wager my soul.

00:05:53.460 --> 00:05:56.970
Good. And I shall wager Kakyoin's.

00:05:59.470 --> 00:06:04.140
I have retrieved my Stand
Atum's arm from your arm.

00:06:04.840 --> 00:06:07.490
Now that I have Kakyoin's soul,

00:06:07.490 --> 00:06:11.110
there's no point in holding
on to your arm anymore.

00:06:11.570 --> 00:06:13.770
It would put my Stand at a disadvantage

00:06:13.770 --> 00:06:17.530
to fight you with only one arm.

00:06:17.980 --> 00:06:22.070
Your Star Platinum's movements are
extremely fast and super precise.

00:06:24.060 --> 00:06:27.270
But to think that you'd pick this baseball game...

00:06:29.360 --> 00:06:32.500
This is the game I'm best at.

00:06:32.500 --> 00:06:39.030
D'Arby! As soon as you lose
to Jotaro, I will finish you.

00:06:39.030 --> 00:06:40.640
Remember that.

00:06:45.740 --> 00:06:47.710
Kaboom

00:06:45.740 --> 00:06:48.230
Oh! That's A Baseball!

00:06:51.330 --> 00:06:53.890
There is no trickery in this game.

00:06:53.890 --> 00:06:55.150
I've confirmed that.

00:06:56.500 --> 00:06:59.010
First, please pick your team.

00:07:01.220 --> 00:07:02.320
The Jaguars.

00:07:02.980 --> 00:07:04.430
Jaguars!

00:07:05.650 --> 00:07:06.950
I see.

00:07:06.950 --> 00:07:10.180
So you've chosen a team with a strong offense.

00:07:10.720 --> 00:07:13.280
Two of your players have
batting averages over .400.

00:07:13.280 --> 00:07:16.550
Then I shall choose the Red Dragons.

00:07:16.550 --> 00:07:18.570
Red Dragons!

00:07:19.560 --> 00:07:22.340
Would you like to bat first
or second? Take your pick.

00:07:23.720 --> 00:07:24.680
First.

00:07:24.680 --> 00:07:28.270
Very well. The Jaguars are up first.

00:07:29.500 --> 00:07:34.080
You can draw your own characters
to input as the players.

00:07:34.990 --> 00:07:37.670
This is Star Platinum.

00:07:39.770 --> 00:07:44.500
Input. Now, let us play ball!

00:07:47.520 --> 00:07:50.660
Jaguars versus Red Dragons.

00:07:50.660 --> 00:07:52.100
Play ball!

00:07:57.030 --> 00:07:59.590
Top of the 1st

00:07:59.910 --> 00:08:05.260
I've chosen #15 to be my pitcher,
since I was born on January 5th.

00:08:08.290 --> 00:08:10.110
Here I go.

00:08:10.560 --> 00:08:11.980
The pitcher is winding up.

00:08:13.980 --> 00:08:15.070
The first pitch!

00:08:16.920 --> 00:08:17.940
What?!

00:08:19.920 --> 00:08:21.070
Strike!

00:08:21.640 --> 00:08:27.060
H-Hey, Jotaro. What did you just do?

00:08:27.060 --> 00:08:31.620
You swung the bat before the
ball even left the pitcher's hand!

00:08:38.170 --> 00:08:43.460
H-Hey, Jotaro... Why do you
keep taking practice swings?

00:08:43.960 --> 00:08:47.680
Don't tell me... Could it be that you...

00:08:48.020 --> 00:08:50.140
Have you played this baseball game—No,

00:08:50.140 --> 00:08:53.170
have you ever played <i>any</i> video game before?

00:08:53.930 --> 00:08:56.170
Answer me, Jotaro!

00:08:56.450 --> 00:08:59.520
Whatever. I know the rules for baseball.

00:08:59.880 --> 00:09:02.030
I'll figure out the controls as I go.

00:09:03.110 --> 00:09:05.320
Wh-What?!

00:09:05.780 --> 00:09:09.130
That ridiculous, terribly-timed swing!

00:09:09.130 --> 00:09:10.860
The way you're working the controls...

00:09:10.860 --> 00:09:13.560
This is your first time playing <i>any</i> game, isn't it?!

00:09:23.370 --> 00:09:25.000
Strike two!

00:09:26.110 --> 00:09:29.710
This time, you swung the bat
after the ball hit the mitt!

00:09:29.710 --> 00:09:31.060
You're a total amateur!

00:09:31.060 --> 00:09:32.810
God damn it, Jotaro!

00:09:32.810 --> 00:09:35.810
You've never played a
video game before, have you?!

00:09:36.350 --> 00:09:38.560
Strike! Batter out!

00:09:39.360 --> 00:09:41.350
Stop messing around, Jotaro!

00:09:41.350 --> 00:09:43.840
Why are you putting on that attitude?!

00:09:43.840 --> 00:09:48.680
You wagered your own soul!
You can't back out now!

00:09:48.680 --> 00:09:50.000
Good grief.

00:09:50.000 --> 00:09:52.130
You should be supportive at times like this.

00:09:52.500 --> 00:09:56.170
"It's just the first inning.
You've only just started.

00:09:56.170 --> 00:09:58.050
You can do it, Jotaro." Like that.

00:09:58.050 --> 00:10:00.040
What are you thinking?

00:10:00.040 --> 00:10:04.340
Even with your Star Platinum's
super precise movements,

00:10:04.340 --> 00:10:09.150
did you think you could beat him with
no knowledge of video games at all?

00:10:10.460 --> 00:10:13.490
What are you thinking, Jotaro?

00:10:13.490 --> 00:10:15.720
What on Earth are you thinking?!

00:10:17.310 --> 00:10:18.270
Jotaro...

00:10:20.020 --> 00:10:22.290
Let me warn you that if, on the other hand,

00:10:22.290 --> 00:10:24.990
this is some plan to trick me
by acting like an amateur,

00:10:24.990 --> 00:10:26.680
it's not going to work.

00:10:27.670 --> 00:10:30.320
No matter the situation,
I never let down my guard.

00:10:30.320 --> 00:10:33.300
Once my opponent has wagered
his soul, even if he is an infant,

00:10:33.300 --> 00:10:34.950
I would give my all to defeat him.

00:10:36.370 --> 00:10:37.310
Old man.

00:10:38.690 --> 00:10:40.740
I'm not thinking about anything.

00:10:41.430 --> 00:10:42.370
Except...

00:10:42.850 --> 00:10:46.590
about breaking that asshole's nose,

00:10:46.590 --> 00:10:52.260
as he sits there so certain that he'll
never lose to anyone in this game.

00:10:52.700 --> 00:10:57.770
I'm only seriously thinking about
getting Kakyoin's soul back.

00:10:59.740 --> 00:11:01.360
You can say what you'd like...

00:11:01.360 --> 00:11:04.150
But it's still the top of the
first inning with one out.

00:11:04.150 --> 00:11:05.900
Let us continue the game.

00:11:06.280 --> 00:11:08.350
Please don't forget that if one of us

00:11:08.350 --> 00:11:12.760
takes an eleven-point lead,
the game will be called.

00:11:17.000 --> 00:11:19.160
Second batter, #3.

00:11:23.530 --> 00:11:24.460
Strike!

00:11:24.740 --> 00:11:27.050
Th-This can't be happening!

00:11:27.050 --> 00:11:29.480
This time, the ball was at
least 40 centimeters away

00:11:29.480 --> 00:11:31.340
from where he swung the bat!

00:11:32.020 --> 00:11:33.430
Strike two!

00:11:33.430 --> 00:11:35.140
Not even close!

00:11:39.300 --> 00:11:41.950
Strike! Batter out!

00:11:43.740 --> 00:11:45.150
It's no use.

00:11:45.150 --> 00:11:47.910
The difference in ability is too obvious.

00:11:47.910 --> 00:11:50.250
At this rate, it's as if a tea ceremony club,

00:11:50.250 --> 00:11:54.450
where nobody's ever held a bat,
decided to challenge a championship team.

00:11:54.810 --> 00:11:56.280
It's too pathetic.

00:11:56.700 --> 00:11:57.450
Strike!

00:11:57.880 --> 00:11:59.420
Strike two!

00:12:00.950 --> 00:12:05.780
It seems he truly is an amateur. He's too weak!

00:12:05.780 --> 00:12:08.510
I think I now understand how a judo master feels

00:12:08.510 --> 00:12:11.310
when he can gauge his opponent's strength simply

00:12:11.310 --> 00:12:13.690
from how he puts on his gi.

00:12:13.690 --> 00:12:17.600
When it comes to video games,
Jotaro is indeed an amateur.

00:12:18.240 --> 00:12:21.730
But I will never let my guard down.

00:12:22.200 --> 00:12:25.350
I've memorized the weaknesses of
all the batters in this game.

00:12:25.980 --> 00:12:28.750
Next will be a low pitch to the outside.

00:12:29.170 --> 00:12:33.860
I'll throw my ultimate screwball and strike
out all three without a single run.

00:12:34.260 --> 00:12:38.030
Top of the first, two outs,
two strikes and no balls.

00:12:38.030 --> 00:12:39.410
Here comes my next pitch.

00:12:39.660 --> 00:12:40.660
Go ahead.

00:12:41.060 --> 00:12:43.910
I've pretty much learned how to bat now.

00:12:44.970 --> 00:12:48.380
What? What did he just say?

00:12:49.520 --> 00:12:52.690
"How to bat"? What?

00:12:53.220 --> 00:12:55.680
Did he just say "pretty much learned"?

00:12:57.390 --> 00:13:00.260
What is he talking about? What does he mean?!

00:13:06.060 --> 00:13:07.230
What?!

00:13:07.230 --> 00:13:08.750
Jotaro!

00:13:08.750 --> 00:13:11.610
Good. This game is pretty fun.

00:13:11.830 --> 00:13:14.360
H-Hey, don't tell me...

00:13:14.360 --> 00:13:17.530
It's still going. The ball is still in the air!

00:13:17.530 --> 00:13:19.570
What did he say just now?!

00:13:19.920 --> 00:13:22.930
"I've pretty much learned how to bat now."

00:13:22.930 --> 00:13:25.330
Learned? Did he just say learned?!

00:13:28.370 --> 00:13:30.240
I-It's fair!

00:13:30.240 --> 00:13:33.110
Y-You're kidding! You're kidding me!

00:13:34.900 --> 00:13:36.280
Home run!

00:13:43.540 --> 00:13:47.040
Home run! A home run!

00:13:49.280 --> 00:13:51.650
Jotaro! You bastard!

00:13:57.300 --> 00:13:59.950
Atum

00:13:57.970 --> 00:13:59.950
D'Arby Younger

00:14:00.950 --> 00:14:02.050
Jotaro!

00:14:02.050 --> 00:14:04.180
What did you just say?

00:14:04.180 --> 00:14:08.170
"Learned"? "I've pretty much learned
how to bat"? Is that what you said?!

00:14:08.500 --> 00:14:10.460
There's no reason for me to say it again.

00:14:13.100 --> 00:14:16.100
He was, without a doubt, a beginner.

00:14:16.510 --> 00:14:20.340
Is he saying that he managed to learn
the controls by swinging eight times?

00:14:21.050 --> 00:14:25.350
Jotaro Kujo has Star Platinum,
who has the power of super precise movement.

00:14:25.770 --> 00:14:27.590
Now I know exactly why

00:14:27.590 --> 00:14:31.020
Lord DIO sees him as a problem,
and why my brother lost.

00:14:35.610 --> 00:14:39.450
Interesting. This is how my opponents should be.

00:14:40.110 --> 00:14:42.540
And you exposed this fearsome

00:14:42.540 --> 00:14:47.910
characteristic of yours in the top of
the first inning, right after we started...

00:14:47.910 --> 00:14:51.120
You'll eventually regret that.

00:14:53.900 --> 00:14:56.380
Let us continue the game, Jotaro.

00:15:01.310 --> 00:15:03.100
He did it!

00:15:03.390 --> 00:15:05.130
It's fair! It's fair!

00:15:05.130 --> 00:15:07.580
He got another home run!

00:15:07.580 --> 00:15:10.320
Now it's four to nothing in the top of the first.

00:15:10.320 --> 00:15:14.520
Looks like you've got the
hang of this game, Jotaro.

00:15:14.520 --> 00:15:16.860
Keep this up! Keep it up!

00:15:17.130 --> 00:15:18.980
Hey, D'Arby.

00:15:18.980 --> 00:15:22.950
I'm sure you don't want to hear this,
but I'll say it as a kindness.

00:15:23.310 --> 00:15:29.120
If you return Kakyoin's soul
right now and take us to DIO,

00:15:23.820 --> 00:15:29.410
Menacing

00:15:29.120 --> 00:15:31.800
we'll spare your life.

00:15:38.800 --> 00:15:41.900
My brother was a master at gambling,

00:15:41.900 --> 00:15:44.080
and a master at cheating.

00:15:45.490 --> 00:15:55.020
Yet he never said to me, "Brother,
why don't we play a game of poker?"

00:15:55.020 --> 00:15:56.440
Not even once.

00:15:57.250 --> 00:15:58.850
Do you know why that is?

00:16:00.730 --> 00:16:06.360
When I was fifteen,
my brother hit on my girlfriend.

00:16:06.360 --> 00:16:09.720
I beat the shit out of him,
even though he was ten years older.

00:16:09.720 --> 00:16:13.220
I broke his ribs and kicked him
until he vomited blood.

00:16:13.220 --> 00:16:16.460
To that, all my brother
had to say was, "I'm sorry."

00:16:17.060 --> 00:16:18.620
Do you know why?

00:16:18.980 --> 00:16:20.920
What are you getting at, you bastard?

00:16:21.170 --> 00:16:26.740
My brother knew ever since we were children
that he had no way of beating me.

00:16:26.740 --> 00:16:29.430
He knew there was a reason he couldn't win.

00:16:30.990 --> 00:16:36.060
And now, it appears as if Jotaro is getting
excited and really taking off with this game.

00:16:36.060 --> 00:16:40.680
However, he's uncertain,
just like my brother was as a child.

00:16:40.880 --> 00:16:43.870
He's uncertain about my abilities.

00:16:43.870 --> 00:16:47.690
"Nah, it couldn't be. Or wait, maybe..."
That's what he's been thinking.

00:16:47.690 --> 00:16:49.130
Right, Jotaro?

00:16:49.130 --> 00:16:50.950
What the hell are you talking about?

00:16:53.390 --> 00:16:57.970
I'm changing pitchers! I'll switch #15 for #77.

